df-tsk
blocks.content: The class of all Tarski classes. Tarski classes is a phrase coined by Grzegorz Bancerek in his article _Tarski's Classes and Ranks_, Journal of Formalized Mathematics, Vol 1, No 3, May-August 1990. A Tarski class is a set whose existence is ensured by Tarski's axiom A (see ~ ax-groth and the equivalent axioms). Axiom A was first presented in Tarski's article _Über unerreichbare Kardinalzahlen_. Tarski introduced the axiom A to enable ZFC to manage inaccessible cardinals. Later Grothendieck introduced the concept of Grothendieck universes and showed they were equal to transitive Tarski classes. (Contributed by FL, 30-Dec-2010.)

thm eltskg(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1) {
  |- wi(wcel(c0, c1), wb(wcel(c0, ctsk), wa(wral(s0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wrex(s1, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(s1))))), wral(s0, cpw(c0), wo(wbr(cv(s0), cen, c0), wcel(cv(s0), c0))))))
  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
  -| diffsc(s1, c0)
} = {
  elab2g(hs0, c0, c1, ctsk, wa(wral(s0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wrex(s1, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(s1))))), wral(s0, cpw(c0), wo(wbr(cv(s0), cen, c0), wcel(cv(s0), c0)))), wa(wral(s0, cv(hs0), wa(wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0)), wrex(s1, cv(hs0), wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(s1))))), wral(s0, cpw(cv(hs0)), wo(wbr(cv(s0), cen, cv(hs0)), wcel(cv(s0), cv(hs0))))))
  anbi12d(wceq(cv(hs0), c0), wral(s0, cv(hs0), wa(wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0)), wrex(s1, cv(hs0), wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(s1))))), wral(s0, cpw(cv(hs0)), wo(wbr(cv(s0), cen, cv(hs0)), wcel(cv(s0), cv(hs0)))), wral(s0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wrex(s1, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(s1))))), wral(s0, cpw(c0), wo(wbr(cv(s0), cen, c0), wcel(cv(s0), c0))))
  raleqbi1dv(s0, cv(hs0), c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0)), wrex(s1, cv(hs0), wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(s1)))), wa(wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wrex(s1, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(s1)))))
  anbi12d(wceq(cv(hs0), c0), wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0)), wrex(s1, cv(hs0), wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(s1))), wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wrex(s1, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(s1))))
  sseq2(cv(hs0), c0, cpw(cv(s0)))
  rexeq(s1, cv(hs0), c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(s1)))
  raleqbidv(s0, cpw(cv(hs0)), cpw(c0), wceq(cv(hs0), c0), wo(wbr(cv(s0), cen, cv(hs0)), wcel(cv(s0), cv(hs0))), wo(wbr(cv(s0), cen, c0), wcel(cv(s0), c0)))
  pweq(cv(hs0), c0)
  orbi12d(wceq(cv(hs0), c0), wbr(cv(s0), cen, cv(hs0)), wcel(cv(s0), cv(hs0)), wbr(cv(s0), cen, c0), wcel(cv(s0), c0))
  breq2(cv(hs0), c0, cv(s0), cen)
  eleq2(cv(hs0), c0, cv(s0))
  df-tsk(hs0, s0, s1)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.w(wa(wral(s0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wrex(s1, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(s1))))), wral(s0, cpw(c0), wo(wbr(cv(s0), cen, c0), wcel(cv(s0), c0)))))
  diff.cv.s(s1, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s1, hs0)
  diff.wceq.s(s0, cv(hs0), c0)
  diff.cv.s(s0, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s0, hs0)
  diff.hs0.s(s1)
  diff.hs0.s(s0)
}
blocks.pretty:
thm eltskg(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1) {
  ⊢ (c0 ∈ c1 →(c0 ∈ Tarski ↔(∀(s0 ∈ c0,(P(s0)⊆ c0 ∧ ∃(s1 ∈ c0, P(s0)⊆ s1)))∧ ∀(s0 ∈ P(c0),(s0[≅]c0 ∨ s0 ∈ c0)))))
  ⊣ d(s0, s1)
  ⊣ d(s0, c0)
  ⊣ d(s1, c0)
} = {
  elab2g(hs0, c0, c1, ctsk, (∀(s0 ∈ c0,(P(s0)⊆ c0 ∧ ∃(s1 ∈ c0, P(s0)⊆ s1)))∧ ∀(s0 ∈ P(c0),(s0[≅]c0 ∨ s0 ∈ c0))), (∀(s0 ∈ hs0,(P(s0)⊆ hs0 ∧ ∃(s1 ∈ hs0, P(s0)⊆ s1)))∧ ∀(s0 ∈ P(hs0),(s0[≅]hs0 ∨ s0 ∈ hs0))))
  anbi12d(hs0 = c0, ∀(s0 ∈ hs0,(P(s0)⊆ hs0 ∧ ∃(s1 ∈ hs0, P(s0)⊆ s1))), ∀(s0 ∈ P(hs0),(s0[≅]hs0 ∨ s0 ∈ hs0)), ∀(s0 ∈ c0,(P(s0)⊆ c0 ∧ ∃(s1 ∈ c0, P(s0)⊆ s1))), ∀(s0 ∈ P(c0),(s0[≅]c0 ∨ s0 ∈ c0)))
  raleqbi1dv(s0, hs0, c0, (P(s0)⊆ hs0 ∧ ∃(s1 ∈ hs0, P(s0)⊆ s1)), (P(s0)⊆ c0 ∧ ∃(s1 ∈ c0, P(s0)⊆ s1)))
  anbi12d(hs0 = c0, P(s0)⊆ hs0, ∃(s1 ∈ hs0, P(s0)⊆ s1), P(s0)⊆ c0, ∃(s1 ∈ c0, P(s0)⊆ s1))
  sseq2(hs0, c0, P(s0))
  rexeq(s1, hs0, c0, P(s0)⊆ s1)
  raleqbidv(s0, P(hs0), P(c0), hs0 = c0, (s0[≅]hs0 ∨ s0 ∈ hs0), (s0[≅]c0 ∨ s0 ∈ c0))
  pweq(hs0, c0)
  orbi12d(hs0 = c0, s0[≅]hs0, s0 ∈ hs0, s0[≅]c0, s0 ∈ c0)
  breq2(hs0, c0, s0, cen)
  eleq2(hs0, c0, s0)
  df-tsk(hs0, s0, s1)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.w((∀(s0 ∈ c0,(P(s0)⊆ c0 ∧ ∃(s1 ∈ c0, P(s0)⊆ s1)))∧ ∀(s0 ∈ P(c0),(s0[≅]c0 ∨ s0 ∈ c0))))
  diff.cv.s(s1, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s1, hs0)
  diff.wceq.s(s0, hs0, c0)
  diff.cv.s(s0, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s0, hs0)
  diff.hs0.s(s1)
  diff.hs0.s(s0)
}

  3imtr4i(wral(s0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wrex(hs0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0))))), wral(s0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wcel(cpw(cv(s0)), c0))), wa(wral(s0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0)), wral(s0, c0, wrex(hs0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0))))), wa(wral(s0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0)), wral(s0, c0, wcel(cpw(cv(s0)), c0))))
  imdistani(wral(s0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0)), wral(s0, c0, wrex(hs0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0)))), wral(s0, c0, wcel(cpw(cv(s0)), c0)))
  ralimdaa(s0, c0, wral(s0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0)), wrex(hs0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0))), wcel(cpw(cv(s0)), c0))
  nfra1(s0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0))
  rexlimdva(hs0, c0, wa(wral(s0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0)), wcel(cv(s0), c0)), wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0)), wcel(cpw(cv(s0)), c0))
  syl(wa(wa(wral(s0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0)), wcel(cv(s0), c0)), wcel(cv(hs0), c0)), wi(wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0)), wcel(cpw(cv(s0)), c0)), wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0))
  adantlr(wral(s0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0)), wcel(cv(s0), c0), wcel(cv(hs0), c0), wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0))
  rspccva(s0, c0, cv(hs0), wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0))
  sseq1d(cpw(cv(s0)), c0, cpw(cv(hs0)), wceq(cv(s0), cv(hs0)))
  pweq(cv(s0), cv(hs0))
  syl5bir(wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0), wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0)), wcel(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wcel(cpw(cv(s0)), cpw(cv(hs0))))
  elpw(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0))
  vpwex(s0)
  ssel(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0, cpw(cv(s0)))
  r19.26(s0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wrex(hs0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0))))
  r19.26(s0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wcel(cpw(cv(s0)), c0))
  ralimi(s0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wcel(cpw(cv(s0)), c0)), wa(wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wrex(hs0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0)))))
  anim2i(wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wcel(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wrex(hs0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0))))
  mpan2(wcel(cpw(cv(s0)), c0), wrex(hs0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0))), wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cpw(cv(s0))))
  ssid(cpw(cv(s0)))
  rspcev(hs0, cpw(cv(s0)), c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cpw(cv(s0))), wss(cpw(cv(s0)), cv(hs0)))

  diff.hs0.w(wa(wral(s0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(s0)), c0)), wcel(cv(s0), c0)))

blocks.name: tskpwss
blocks.content: First axiom of a Tarski class. The subsets of an element of a Tarski class belong to the class. (Contributed by FL, 30-Dec-2010.) (Proof shortened by Mario Carneiro, 20-Sep-2014.)
blocks.origin:
thm tskpwss(class c0, class c1) {
  |- wi(wa(wcel(c0, ctsk), wcel(c1, c0)), wss(cpw(c1), c0))
} = {
  sylan(wcel(c0, ctsk), wcel(c1, c0), wss(cpw(c1), c0), wral(hs0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0)))
  syl(wcel(c0, ctsk), wral(hs0, c0, wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0)), wral(hs0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0), wrex(hs1, c0, wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), cv(hs1))))))
  simpld(wcel(c0, ctsk), wral(hs0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0), wrex(hs1, c0, wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), cv(hs1))))), wral(hs0, cpw(c0), wo(wbr(cv(hs0), cen, c0), wcel(cv(hs0), c0))))
  ibi(wcel(c0, ctsk), wa(wral(hs0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0), wrex(hs1, c0, wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), cv(hs1))))), wral(hs0, cpw(c0), wo(wbr(cv(hs0), cen, c0), wcel(cv(hs0), c0)))))
  eltskg(hs0, hs1, c0, ctsk)
  ralimi(hs0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0), wrex(hs1, c0, wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), cv(hs1)))), wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0))
  simpl(wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0), wrex(hs1, c0, wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), cv(hs1))))
  rspccva(hs0, c0, c1, wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0), wss(cpw(c1), c0))
  sseq1d(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0, cpw(c1), wceq(cv(hs0), c1))
  pweq(cv(hs0), c1)
  diff.hs0.s(hs1)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs1.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(c1)
  diff.hs0.w(wss(cpw(c1), c0))
}

thm tskpwss(class c0, class c1) {
  ⊢ ((c0 ∈ Tarski ∧ c1 ∈ c0)→ P(c1)⊆ c0)
} = {
  sylan(c0 ∈ Tarski, c1 ∈ c0, P(c1)⊆ c0, ∀(hs0 ∈ c0, P(hs0)⊆ c0))
  syl(c0 ∈ Tarski, ∀(hs0 ∈ c0, P(hs0)⊆ c0), ∀(hs0 ∈ c0,(P(hs0)⊆ c0 ∧ ∃(hs1 ∈ c0, P(hs0)⊆ hs1))))
  simpld(c0 ∈ Tarski, ∀(hs0 ∈ c0,(P(hs0)⊆ c0 ∧ ∃(hs1 ∈ c0, P(hs0)⊆ hs1))), ∀(hs0 ∈ P(c0),(hs0[≅]c0 ∨ hs0 ∈ c0)))
  ibi(c0 ∈ Tarski, (∀(hs0 ∈ c0,(P(hs0)⊆ c0 ∧ ∃(hs1 ∈ c0, P(hs0)⊆ hs1)))∧ ∀(hs0 ∈ P(c0),(hs0[≅]c0 ∨ hs0 ∈ c0))))
  eltskg(hs0, hs1, c0, ctsk)
  ralimi(hs0, c0, (P(hs0)⊆ c0 ∧ ∃(hs1 ∈ c0, P(hs0)⊆ hs1)), P(hs0)⊆ c0)
  simpl(P(hs0)⊆ c0, ∃(hs1 ∈ c0, P(hs0)⊆ hs1))
  rspccva(hs0, c0, c1, P(hs0)⊆ c0, P(c1)⊆ c0)
  sseq1d(P(hs0), c0, P(c1), hs0 = c1)
  pweq(hs0, c1)
  diff.hs0.s(hs1)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs1.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(c1)
  diff.hs0.w(P(c1)⊆ c0)
}

blocks.name: tskpw
blocks.content: Second axiom of a Tarski class. The powerset of an element of a Tarski class belongs to the class. (Contributed by FL, 30-Dec-2010.) (Proof shortened by Mario Carneiro, 20-Sep-2014.)
blocks.origin:
thm tskpw(class c0, class c1) {
  |- wi(wa(wcel(c0, ctsk), wcel(c1, c0)), wcel(cpw(c1), c0))
} = {
  sylan(wcel(c0, ctsk), wcel(c1, c0), wcel(cpw(c1), c0), wral(hs0, c0, wcel(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0)))
  syl(wcel(c0, ctsk), wral(hs0, c0, wcel(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0)), wral(hs0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0), wcel(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0))))
  simpld(wcel(c0, ctsk), wral(hs0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0), wcel(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0))), wral(hs0, cpw(c0), wo(wbr(cv(hs0), cen, c0), wcel(cv(hs0), c0))))
  ibi(wcel(c0, ctsk), wa(wral(hs0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0), wcel(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0))), wral(hs0, cpw(c0), wo(wbr(cv(hs0), cen, c0), wcel(cv(hs0), c0)))))
  eltsk2g(hs0, c0, ctsk)
  ralimi(hs0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0), wcel(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0)), wcel(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0))
  simpr(wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0), wcel(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0))
  rspccva(hs0, c0, c1, wcel(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0), wcel(cpw(c1), c0))
  eleq1d(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0, cpw(c1), wceq(cv(hs0), c1))
  pweq(cv(hs0), c1)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(c1)
  diff.hs0.w(wcel(cpw(c1), c0))
}

thm tskpw(class c0, class c1) {
  ⊢ ((c0 ∈ Tarski ∧ c1 ∈ c0)→ P(c1)∈ c0)
} = {
  sylan(c0 ∈ Tarski, c1 ∈ c0, P(c1)∈ c0, ∀(hs0 ∈ c0, P(hs0)∈ c0))
  syl(c0 ∈ Tarski, ∀(hs0 ∈ c0, P(hs0)∈ c0), ∀(hs0 ∈ c0,(P(hs0)⊆ c0 ∧ P(hs0)∈ c0)))
  simpld(c0 ∈ Tarski, ∀(hs0 ∈ c0,(P(hs0)⊆ c0 ∧ P(hs0)∈ c0)), ∀(hs0 ∈ P(c0),(hs0[≅]c0 ∨ hs0 ∈ c0)))
  ibi(c0 ∈ Tarski, (∀(hs0 ∈ c0,(P(hs0)⊆ c0 ∧ P(hs0)∈ c0))∧ ∀(hs0 ∈ P(c0),(hs0[≅]c0 ∨ hs0 ∈ c0))))
  eltsk2g(hs0, c0, ctsk)
  ralimi(hs0, c0, (P(hs0)⊆ c0 ∧ P(hs0)∈ c0), P(hs0)∈ c0)
  simpr(P(hs0)⊆ c0, P(hs0)∈ c0)
  rspccva(hs0, c0, c1, P(hs0)∈ c0, P(c1)∈ c0)
  eleq1d(P(hs0), c0, P(c1), hs0 = c1)
  pweq(hs0, c1)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(c1)
  diff.hs0.w(P(c1)∈ c0)
}

blocks.name: tsken
blocks.content: Third axiom of a Tarski class. A subset of a Tarski class is either equipotent to the class or an element of the class. (Contributed by FL, 30-Dec-2010.) (Revised by Mario Carneiro, 20-Sep-2014.)
blocks.origin:
thm tsken(class c0, class c1) {
  |- wi(wa(wcel(c0, ctsk), wss(c1, c0)), wo(wbr(c1, cen, c0), wcel(c1, c0)))
} = {
  syl2an2r(wcel(c0, ctsk), wss(c1, c0), wo(wbr(c1, cen, c0), wcel(c1, c0)), wral(hs0, cpw(c0), wo(wbr(cv(hs0), cen, c0), wcel(cv(hs0), c0))), wcel(c1, cpw(c0)))
  simprd(wcel(c0, ctsk), wral(hs0, cpw(c0), wo(wbr(cv(hs0), cen, c0), wcel(cv(hs0), c0))), wral(hs0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0), wrex(hs1, c0, wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), cv(hs1))))))
  ibi(wcel(c0, ctsk), wa(wral(hs0, c0, wa(wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), c0), wrex(hs1, c0, wss(cpw(cv(hs0)), cv(hs1))))), wral(hs0, cpw(c0), wo(wbr(cv(hs0), cen, c0), wcel(cv(hs0), c0)))))

blocks.name: rankcf
blocks.content: Any set must be at least as large as the cofinality of its rank, because the ranks of the elements of ` A ` form a cofinal map into ` ( rank `` A ) ` . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 27-May-2013.)

blocks.name: r1tskina
blocks.content: There is a direct relationship between transitive Tarski classes and inaccessible cardinals: the Tarski classes that occur in the cumulative hierarchy are exactly at the strongly inaccessible cardinals. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 8-Jun-2013.)
blocks.origin:

blocks.name: tskint
blocks.content: The intersection of an element of a transitive Tarski class is an element of the class. (Contributed by FL, 17-Apr-2011.) (Revised by Mario Carneiro, 20-Sep-2014.)

blocks.name: tskun
blocks.content: The union of two elements of a transitive Tarski class is in the set. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 20-Sep-2014.)

blocks.name: tskxp
blocks.content: The Cartesian product of two elements of a transitive Tarski class is an element of the class. JFM CLASSES2 th. 67 (partly). (Contributed by FL, 15-Apr-2011.) (Proof shortened by Mario Carneiro, 20-Sep-2014.)

blocks.content: A transitive Tarski class is closed under small unions. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 22-Jun-2013.)
